---
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "Bobby Charlton — Every Cloud Has a Silver Lining";
const description = "The Munich air disaster left him miraculously alive. The guilt of a survivor, the promise to fallen friends, the weight of a nation. How resilience became the defining force of the greatest English footballer of all time.";
const date = "May 2025";
const readTime = "12 min read";
const author = "Francesco B.";

const teammates = [
  { name: "George Best",     slug: "best-george",     role: "RW", trait: "The Fifth Beatle" },
  { name: "Denis Law",       slug: "law-denis",       role: "ST", trait: "The King" },
  { name: "Nobby Stiles",    slug: "stiles-nobby",    role: "DM", trait: "The Terrier" },
];
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/>
  <title>{title} – Legends Database</title>
  <meta name="description" content={description}/>
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow"/>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://legendsdatabase.com/articles/bobby-charlton"/>
  <meta property="og:type"         content="article"/>
  <meta property="og:url"          content="https://legendsdatabase.com/articles/bobby-charlton"/>
  <meta property="og:title"        content={title}/>
  <meta property="og:description"  content={description}/>
  <meta property="og:image"        content="https://legendsdatabase.com/articles/bobbycharlton_article.jpg"/>
  <meta property="og:image:width"  content="1200"/>
  <meta property="og:image:height" content="630"/>
  <meta property="og:locale"       content="en_US"/>
  <meta name="twitter:card"        content="summary_large_image"/>
  <meta name="twitter:title"       content={title}/>
  <meta name="twitter:description" content={description}/>
  <meta name="twitter:image"       content="https://legendsdatabase.com/articles/bobbycharlton_article.jpg"/>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png"/>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,700;1,700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <style is:global>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, 'SF Pro Text', 'Inter', sans-serif;
      background: #f2f2f7;
      color: #1d1d1f;
      padding-top: 44px;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }

    /* ── HERO ── */
    .hero-image-wrap {
      width: 100%;
      height: clamp(320px, 55vw, 580px);
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
    }
    .hero-image {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      object-position: center 20%;
      display: block;
      filter: brightness(0.60);
      transition: transform 8s ease;
    }
    .hero-image-wrap:hover .hero-image { transform: scale(1.03); }
    .hero-overlay {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent 20%, rgba(0,0,0,0.72) 100%);
    }
    .hero-caption {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 28px;
      left: 40px;
      right: 40px;
    }
    .hero-eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .hero-eyebrow-dot { width: 4px; height: 4px; border-radius: 50%; background: #cc0000; }
    .hero-title {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: clamp(22px, 5vw, 50px);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.5px;
      line-height: 1.1;
      color: #ffffff;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }
    .hero-title em { font-style: italic; color: rgba(255,200,200,0.85); }
    .hero-meta {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 12px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    .hero-meta-sep { opacity: 0.4; }
    .hero-author { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.70); font-weight: 500; }

    /* ── LAYOUT ── */
    .article-wrap {
      flex: 1;
      max-width: 720px;
      width: 100%;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 52px 40px 80px;
    }
    .back-link {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: #6e6e73;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      transition: color 0.15s;
    }
    .back-link:hover { color: #cc0000; }

    /* ── PROSE ── */
    .prose p {
      font-size: 16.5px;
      line-height: 1.82;
      color: #3a3a3c;
      margin-bottom: 26px;
    }
    .prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .prose strong { color: #1d1d1f; font-weight: 600; }
    .prose em { font-style: italic; color: #1d1d1f; }
    .prose a {
      color: #cc0000;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(204,0,0,0.25);
      transition: border-color 0.15s;
    }
    .prose a:hover { border-color: #cc0000; }

    /* ── SECTION HEADING ── */
    .section-heading { margin: 52px 0 18px; }
    .section-heading-accent {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 24px;
      height: 3px;
      background: #cc0000;
      border-radius: 2px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .section-heading h2 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 26px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.3px;
      color: #1d1d1f;
      line-height: 1.25;
    }

    /* ── PULL QUOTE ── */
    .pull-quote {
      margin: 44px 0;
      padding: 30px 36px;
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 18px;
      border-left: 4px solid #cc0000;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .pull-quote::before {
      content: '"';
      position: absolute;
      top: 10px;
      right: 24px;
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 80px;
      color: #cc0000;
      opacity: 0.08;
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .pull-quote-text {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 19px;
      font-style: italic;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: #1d1d1f;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .pull-quote-attr {
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #aeaeb2;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    /* ── DARK QUOTE ── */
    .dark-quote {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d0005, #1a0008);
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 30px 32px;
      margin: 44px 0;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .dark-quote::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      right: -30px;
      bottom: -30px;
      width: 140px;
      height: 140px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: rgba(204,0,0,0.10);
    }
    .dark-quote-label {
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #cc0000;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .dark-quote-text {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 18px;
      font-style: italic;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #ffffff;
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .dark-quote-attr {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    /* ── PLAYER CARD INLINE ── */
    .player-card-inline {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 16px;
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 18px 20px;
      margin: 32px 0;
      text-decoration: none;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
      border: 1.5px solid transparent;
      transition: border-color 0.15s, transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
    }
    .player-card-inline:hover {
      border-color: #cc0000;
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.09);
    }
    .player-card-inline-badge {
      width: 48px;
      height: 48px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #cc0000, #ff3333);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: #fff;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .player-card-inline-body { flex: 1; }
    .player-card-inline-name { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #1d1d1f; margin-bottom: 3px; }
    .player-card-inline-sub { font-size: 12px; color: #aeaeb2; }
    .player-card-inline-arrow { font-size: 16px; color: #aeaeb2; transition: color 0.15s, transform 0.15s; }
    .player-card-inline:hover .player-card-inline-arrow { color: #cc0000; transform: translateX(3px); }

    /* ── STAT STRIP ── */
    .stat-strip {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
      margin: 40px 0;
    }
    .stat-box {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 18px 14px;
      text-align: center;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    }
    .stat-val {
      font-size: 26px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -1px;
      color: #cc0000;
      line-height: 1;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }
    .stat-lbl {
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #aeaeb2;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    /* ── MUNICH BOX — special treatment ── */
    .munich-box {
      background: #1a1a1a;
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 32px;
      margin: 44px 0;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    }
    .munich-box::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 30% 50%, rgba(204,0,0,0.08) 0%, transparent 70%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    .munich-date {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
    }
    .munich-date-line {
      flex: 1;
      height: 1px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    }
    .munich-title {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 22px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #ffffff;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      line-height: 1.3;
    }
    .munich-body {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
      line-height: 1.75;
    }
    .munich-stats {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 22px;
    }
    .munich-stat {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 14px 12px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .munich-stat-val {
      font-size: 24px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #cc0000;
      letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    }
    .munich-stat-lbl {
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-top: 4px;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    /* ── QUALITIES GRID ── */
    .qualities-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
      margin: 32px 0;
    }
    .quality-card {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 18px 16px;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
      text-align: center;
      border-top: 3px solid transparent;
    }
    .quality-card.red { border-top-color: #cc0000; }
    .quality-card.gray { border-top-color: #aeaeb2; }
    .quality-icon { font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .quality-title { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #1d1d1f; margin-bottom: 4px; }
    .quality-body { font-size: 11px; color: #6e6e73; line-height: 1.5; }

    /* ── BROTHERS BOX ── */
    .brothers-box {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 28px 24px;
      margin: 40px 0;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    }
    .brothers-title {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #aeaeb2;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 22px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .brothers-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
      align-items: start;
    }
    .brother-side { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
    .brother-side.right { align-items: flex-end; }
    .brother-name { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #1d1d1f; }
    .brother-role {
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 700;
      padding: 3px 9px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      display: inline-block;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .brother-role.red { background: #fff0ee; color: #cc0000; }
    .brother-role.gray { background: #f5f5f7; color: #6e6e73; }
    .brother-desc { font-size: 12px; color: #6e6e73; line-height: 1.55; }
    .brother-vs {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 6px;
      padding-top: 8px;
    }
    .brother-vs-line { width: 1px; height: 30px; background: #e5e5ea; }
    .brother-vs-text { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 800; color: #aeaeb2; }

    /* ── TEAMMATES ── */
    .teammates-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
      margin: 24px 0 32px;
    }
    .teammate-card {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 16px;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
      text-decoration: none;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 6px;
      border: 1.5px solid transparent;
      transition: border-color 0.15s, transform 0.15s;
    }
    .teammate-card:hover { border-color: #cc0000; transform: translateY(-2px); }
    .teammate-role {
      font-size: 9.5px;
      font-weight: 700;
      padding: 2px 7px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      display: inline-block;
      background: #fff0ee;
      color: #cc0000;
      align-self: flex-start;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .teammate-name { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #1d1d1f; line-height: 1.3; }
    .teammate-trait { font-size: 11px; color: #aeaeb2; font-style: italic; }
    .teammate-arrow { font-size: 11px; color: #cc0000; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.15s; }
    .teammate-card:hover .teammate-arrow { opacity: 1; }

    /* ── TIMELINE ── */
    .career-timeline {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 28px 24px;
      margin: 40px 0;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    }
    .timeline-title {
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #aeaeb2;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 22px;
    }
    .timeline-item {
      display: flex;
      gap: 16px;
      padding-bottom: 22px;
      position: relative;
    }
    .timeline-item:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }
    .timeline-item::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      left: 11px;
      top: 26px;
      bottom: 0;
      width: 1px;
      background: #f0f0f5;
    }
    .timeline-item:last-child::before { display: none; }
    .timeline-dot {
      width: 24px;
      height: 24px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: #cc0000;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      margin-top: 2px;
    }
    .timeline-dot-inner { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #fff; }
    .timeline-dot.dim { background: #e5e5ea; }
    .timeline-dot.gold { background: #c8a800; }
    .timeline-dot.black { background: #1d1d1f; }
    .timeline-content { flex: 1; }
    .timeline-year { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: #aeaeb2; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 3px; }
    .timeline-event { font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 600; color: #1d1d1f; margin-bottom: 3px; line-height: 1.3; }
    .timeline-sub { font-size: 12px; color: #6e6e73; line-height: 1.5; }

    /* ── HIGHLIGHT BOX ── */
    .highlight-box {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d0005, #1a0008);
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 28px 32px;
      margin: 40px 0;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .highlight-box::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      right: -20px;
      top: -20px;
      width: 120px;
      height: 120px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: rgba(204,0,0,0.12);
    }
    .highlight-box-label {
      font-size: 10px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #cc0000;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .highlight-box-text {
      font-size: 17px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #ffffff;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    /* ── DIVIDER ── */
    .prose-divider {
      height: 1px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, #e5e5ea, transparent);
      margin: 52px 0;
    }

    /* ── FADE IN ── */
    .fade-in {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(16px);
      transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease;
    }
    .fade-in.visible { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }

    /* ── MOBILE ── */
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .hero-caption { left: 20px; right: 20px; bottom: 20px; }
      .hero-title { font-size: clamp(20px, 7vw, 32px); }
      .article-wrap { padding: 32px 20px 64px; }
      .prose p { font-size: 15.5px; }
      .pull-quote { padding: 22px 20px; }
      .pull-quote-text { font-size: 17px; }
      .dark-quote { padding: 22px 20px; }
      .dark-quote-text { font-size: 16px; }
      .stat-strip { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
      .munich-stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
      .qualities-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
      .brothers-row { gap: 10px; }
      .brother-desc { font-size: 11px; }
      .teammates-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
      .section-heading h2 { font-size: 22px; }
      .highlight-box { padding: 22px 20px; }
      .highlight-box-text { font-size: 15px; }
      .munich-box { padding: 22px 20px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <Navbar/>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero-image-wrap">
    <img
      src="/articles/bobbycharlton_article.jpg"
      alt="Bobby Charlton — Every Cloud Has a Silver Lining"
      class="hero-image"
    />
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-caption">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">
        <span class="hero-eyebrow-dot"></span>
        Player Profile
        <span class="hero-eyebrow-dot"></span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Bobby Charlton<br/><em>Every Cloud Has a Silver Lining</em></h1>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <span class="hero-author">{author}</span>
        <span class="hero-meta-sep">·</span>
        <span>{date}</span>
        <span class="hero-meta-sep">·</span>
        <span>{readTime}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ARTICLE -->
  <div class="article-wrap">
    <a href="/articles" class="back-link">← Articles</a>

    <!-- INTRO — THE IDIOM -->
    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>In the English language, there is a widely used saying: <em>"Every cloud has a silver lining."</em> The origin is attributed to the renowned English poet John Milton, who first used it in his 1634 work, <em>Comus</em>. The meaning: just as a dark cloud, when illuminated by the sun, reveals a bright silver outline, it is possible to find positive aspects even in the darkest and most tragic situations.</p>
      <p>In our language, there is a word — recently overused, perhaps even excessively so — that encapsulates this concept well: <strong>resilience</strong>.</p>
      <p>When I think of Bobby Charlton, the first word that comes to mind is precisely that.</p>
    </div>

    <a href="/player/charlton-robert" class="player-card-inline fade-in">
      <div class="player-card-inline-badge">CM</div>
      <div class="player-card-inline-body">
        <div class="player-card-inline-name">Sir Bobby Charlton</div>
        <div class="player-card-inline-sub">CM · England · Manchester United · 1956–1973</div>
      </div>
      <div class="player-card-inline-arrow">→</div>
    </a>

    <!-- STATS -->
    <div class="stat-strip fade-in">
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-val">106</div>
        <div class="stat-lbl">England caps</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-val">49</div>
        <div class="stat-lbl">International goals</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-val">758</div>
        <div class="stat-lbl">United appearances</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-val">3</div>
        <div class="stat-lbl">Major titles won</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-divider fade-in"></div>

    <!-- MUNICH -->
    <div class="section-heading fade-in">
      <div class="section-heading-accent"></div>
      <h2>6 February 1958 — The Day That Changed Everything</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>In 1958, Bobby Charlton was just 21 years old — a promising young talent like many others. He had already been with Manchester United for five years, signed at the direct request of the legendary <strong>Matt Busby</strong>, who spotted him as a young boy playing for an East Northumberland schools' representative team.</p>
      <p>Manchester United was on a return flight from Belgrade, where they had played a European Cup match against Red Star. That United squad was young, immensely talented, and full of potential — the <strong>Busby Babes</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- MUNICH BLACK BOX -->
    <div class="munich-box fade-in">
      <div class="munich-date">
        <div class="munich-date-line"></div>
        Munich Air Disaster · 6 February 1958
        <div class="munich-date-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="munich-title">The Third Attempt to Take Off Was Fatal</div>
      <div class="munich-body">Before returning to Manchester, the plane stopped in Munich for refuelling. Heavy snowfall, icy winds, and extremely poor visibility made conditions treacherous. After two failed attempts to take off — due to mechanical issues — the aircraft failed to gain altitude in time, crashed into a house, and came to a violent halt. Bobby Charlton was found miraculously alive, suffering only a minor head injury, still strapped to his seat.</div>
      <div class="munich-stats">
        <div class="munich-stat">
          <div class="munich-stat-val">44</div>
          <div class="munich-stat-lbl">People on board</div>
        </div>
        <div class="munich-stat">
          <div class="munich-stat-val">23</div>
          <div class="munich-stat-lbl">Lost their lives</div>
        </div>
        <div class="munich-stat">
          <div class="munich-stat-val">8</div>
          <div class="munich-stat-lbl">United players killed</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>Charlton only learned about the deaths of his teammates and close friends while in the hospital. This moment became a turning point in his life. Psychologically, he never fully recovered. He considered himself a miracle survivor, but he never came to terms with the fact that he had lived while his friends had not.</p>
      <p>And this is where resilience came into play. Instead of falling into despair, instead of being consumed by darkness, the <em>"miner's son"</em> rolled up his sleeves, gritted his teeth, and vowed to carry on — for the friends and teammates who were no longer there.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="pull-quote fade-in">
      <div class="pull-quote-text">"He was one of the greatest players I have ever seen, the heartbeat of my World Cup-winning team in 1966."</div>
      <div class="pull-quote-attr">— Sir Alf Ramsey, on Duncan Edwards</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-divider fade-in"></div>

    <!-- THE MAN -->
    <div class="section-heading fade-in">
      <div class="section-heading-accent"></div>
      <h2>The English Gentleman</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>Bobby Charlton embodied the very essence of the English gentleman — a man from another era. Calm, reserved, composed, yet also tenacious, determined, and relentlessly professional. Loved by his teammates and respected by his opponents.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="qualities-grid fade-in">
      <div class="quality-card red">
        <div class="quality-icon">⚡</div>
        <div class="quality-title">Technically Gifted</div>
        <div class="quality-body">Could shoot with either foot effortlessly. Outstanding vision and superb technical ability.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="quality-card red">
        <div class="quality-icon">🧠</div>
        <div class="quality-title">Mentally Formidable</div>
        <div class="quality-body">Survived Munich. Carried the weight of fallen friends. Never let it break him — let it drive him.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="quality-card red">
        <div class="quality-icon">🤝</div>
        <div class="quality-title">A True Gentleman</div>
        <div class="quality-body">Never "soft" — simply measured and dignified. Loved by teammates, respected by every opponent.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="quality-card gray">
        <div class="quality-icon">🎯</div>
        <div class="quality-title">Natural Goalscorer</div>
        <div class="quality-body">A natural instinct for goal. 249 goals for United, 49 for England. Scored in every major occasion.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="quality-card gray">
        <div class="quality-icon">🔄</div>
        <div class="quality-title">Versatile</div>
        <div class="quality-body">Started as a right-sided inside forward, evolved to midfield. Today: a brilliant mezzala or second striker.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="quality-card gray">
        <div class="quality-icon">👑</div>
        <div class="quality-title">Natural Leader</div>
        <div class="quality-body">Exceptional charisma. Gave everything for the team — not through words, but through example.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dark-quote fade-in">
      <div class="dark-quote-label">Franz Beckenbauer</div>
      <div class="dark-quote-text">"I admire Charlton more than any other player — even Pelé."</div>
      <div class="dark-quote-attr">Franz Beckenbauer — recently passed away, 2024</div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE PROMISE -->
    <div class="section-heading fade-in">
      <div class="section-heading-accent"></div>
      <h2>The Promise</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>As Charlton himself later revealed in an interview, his sole motivation in life became <strong>winning an international trophy for the teammates who had not made it</strong>. This desire burned like an eternal flame, driving him to give 100% in every match — but in true English fashion, like a true gentleman.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- CAREER TIMELINE -->
    <div class="career-timeline fade-in">
      <div class="timeline-title">The Road to Fulfilment</div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-inner"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-year">1956</div>
          <div class="timeline-event">Manchester United debut — age 18</div>
          <div class="timeline-sub">Immediately earns his place among the legendary Busby Babes.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot black"><div class="timeline-dot-inner"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-year">6 Feb 1958</div>
          <div class="timeline-event">Munich Air Disaster</div>
          <div class="timeline-sub">Miraculously survives. 8 teammates killed. The promise is made.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot gold"><div class="timeline-dot-inner"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-year">1966</div>
          <div class="timeline-event">World Cup winner — Wembley</div>
          <div class="timeline-sub">England 4-2 West Germany. Two goals from Charlton. The first promise kept.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot gold"><div class="timeline-dot-inner"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-year">1968</div>
          <div class="timeline-event">European Cup winner — Wembley</div>
          <div class="timeline-sub">Manchester United 4-1 Benfica. Two goals. For the first time, the weight lifts.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot dim"><div class="timeline-dot-inner"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-year">1973</div>
          <div class="timeline-event">Retirement from playing</div>
          <div class="timeline-sub">758 appearances, 249 goals for United. One of the greatest careers in English football history.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-dot dim"><div class="timeline-dot-inner"></div></div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <div class="timeline-year">October 2023</div>
          <div class="timeline-event">Passing — age 86</div>
          <div class="timeline-sub">An emblem of resilience, dignity, and everything that is right about football.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box fade-in">
      <div class="highlight-box-label">Wembley, 29 May 1968</div>
      <div class="highlight-box-text">Manchester United crushed Eusébio's Benfica 4-1 in the European Cup final. Charlton scored twice. And for the first time, he admitted feeling incredibly light — as if a massive weight had finally been lifted off his shoulders. His promise had been fulfilled.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-divider fade-in"></div>

    <!-- THE BROTHERS -->
    <div class="section-heading fade-in">
      <div class="section-heading-accent"></div>
      <h2>Bobby & Jack — Two Brothers, One World Cup</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>Charlton was the complete opposite of his brother, Jack Charlton. Jack was a tough, rugged, and uncompromising centre-back — blunt, direct, and hard-edged. A stark contrast to Bobby's temperament. The relationship between the two brothers was notoriously turbulent, with tensions exacerbated by difficult relations between their wives.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="brothers-box fade-in">
      <div class="brothers-title">The Charlton Brothers — 1966 World Cup winners</div>
      <div class="brothers-row">
        <div class="brother-side">
          <div class="brother-name">Bobby Charlton</div>
          <span class="brother-role red">CM / FW</span>
          <div class="brother-desc">Calm, reserved, composed. A gentleman in every sense. Technically gifted, tactically intelligent, emotionally profound.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="brother-vs">
          <div class="brother-vs-line"></div>
          <div class="brother-vs-text">VS</div>
          <div class="brother-vs-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="brother-side right">
          <div class="brother-name">Jack Charlton</div>
          <span class="brother-role gray">CB</span>
          <div class="brother-desc">Rugged, uncompromising, blunt. A quintessentially English defender. His personality reflected his playing style entirely.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>After Jack Charlton's passing in 2020, Bobby openly expressed his grief and affection for his brother, revealing a bond that — despite the difficulties — remained significant to both of them. And let's be honest: how many brothers can say they won a World Cup playing for the same national team?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- TEAMMATES -->
    <div class="section-heading fade-in">
      <div class="section-heading-accent"></div>
      <h2>The Holy Trinity</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>His combination play with the magnificent <a href="/player/best-george">George Best</a> is the stuff of legend. Together with Denis Law, they formed what became known as the Holy Trinity — the three greatest players in Manchester United history, united in a single era.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="teammates-grid fade-in">
      {teammates.map(p => (
        <a href={'/player/' + p.slug} class="teammate-card">
          <span class="teammate-role">{p.role}</span>
          <span class="teammate-name">{p.name}</span>
          <span class="teammate-trait">{p.trait}</span>
          <span class="teammate-arrow">View profile →</span>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="prose-divider fade-in"></div>

    <!-- CONCLUSION -->
    <div class="section-heading fade-in">
      <div class="section-heading-accent"></div>
      <h2>Thank You, Bobby</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>Bobby Charlton was not just a symbol of Manchester United or English football — he was an emblem of resilience and dignity. His career and his life offer a lesson in greatness, proving that it is not defined solely by trophies won, but also by <strong>integrity, courage, and perseverance</strong> in the face of adversity.</p>
      <p>He was a miner's son from Northumberland who survived a plane crash, carried the weight of fallen friends for a decade, and fulfilled his promise on the greatest stages in world football. He did it with grace, with dignity, and without ever raising his voice.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="pull-quote fade-in">
      <div class="pull-quote-text">Greatness is not defined solely by trophies won, but also by integrity, courage, and perseverance in the face of adversity. Bobby Charlton embodied all three.</div>
    </div>

